<br>
Naggy + Vox to list, good idea.  Calendar is a bad spot for them.<br>
<br>
48 hours on lists?  Bad idea.  Remember, the amount of time you're given to kill them isn't *preparation time*, it's *oh god we suck we need to try again and again and again time*.  Preparation time is keeping in touch with who's above you on the list and finding out exactly when the spawn died, paying attention to messages on upcoming patches, etc.<br>
<br>
Not including patches, the 48 hour limit effectively takes away 16 of the 52 Naggy/Vox spawns a year.  And I have a feeling most people will actually use most of that time just because people are lazy.  Do you really want 30% less of a chance of getting a Cloak of Flames, a White Dragon Scale, a Torbin's Eyepatch?  I'll take all the chances I can get.<br>
<br>
Vox &amp; Naggy, 24 hours at most in my opinion.  That's, on average, EIGHT DAYS of preparation time.  At the very least it's TWO DAYS of preparation time.<br>
<br>
Getting used to a 24 hour limit would be good since most of the bigger stuff you'll end up making agreements on later will be 24 or even 12 hour limits.<br>
<br>
The uber mobs in Kunark are already basically on a list.  The problem with making this list open for anybody to jump in is lots of lost spawn time I guess.  Probably best, for now, to simply contact the people you know are killing the mob and attempt to get a shot.  Once you can prove that you can either kill or come close to killing them, simply ask to be put into rotation.<br>
<br>
Closing thoughts..<br>
<br>
It's Verant's job to enforce PnP.  It's our opportunity to never let it get that far.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, I'm watching you open raid people closely (remember, I'm one of the biggest advocates of open raids).  If I see these open raids being cancelled too much, being traded or otherwise abused, your posts on the calendar are going to start disappearing. <p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#000000"><tr><td align="center" colspan="2"><img src="http://everquest.estoncom.com/noj/images/bishsign1.gif" border="0" alt="Get yer foul tallard mouse cursor OFF OF ME!"></td><td rowspan="2" align="center"><font color="#FFFFDD" size="1" face="tempus sans itc">and...</font><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=44611"><font color="#29FF29" face="tempus sans itc" size="3">Kraket</font></a><br><br><font color="#8888FF" face="tempus sans itc" size="2">The<br>narcoleptic <br>lizard</font></td></tr><tr><td align="center" colspan="2"><a href="http://pub30.ezboard.com/bnuggetsofjustice"><font color="#FF0042" face="tempus sans itc" size="2">~ Nuggets of Justice Message Board ~</a></td></tr><tr><td align="center"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3814"><font face="tempus sans itc" color="#0024FF" size="2">Level 52 Vicar</font></a></td><td align="center"><a href="http://pub30.ezboard.com/fnuggetsofjusticefrm3.showMessage?topicID=14.topic"><font color="#00F824" face="tempus sans itc" size="2">Want List</font></a>  </td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usorrowsend.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorrows End</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/01 3:36:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=607.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /raise.</span><hr size=1>     I abuse the calender! If