<br>
What has followed is 'guidelines' of how the calendar should be used above and beyond those simple 2 'rules'. Most of these 'guidelines' have been in place for some time now, and noone had had too much of a problem with it, and some have deviated from it from time to time, but on a whole it's worked well and has been <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fair to all</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Now, that the council of guild's has come back into action, everyone can come and have a chance to rework and tweak the 'guidelines' so that they are as fair as possible to every individual and guild on the server. Quite frankly, I think pushing for fairness and an equal chance is a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> good thing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
The problem is that this stuff is difficult to work out on a message board, and better off done in a meeting where everyone is there in real time and can have the floor to speak where everyone will hear them at that very second. In messageboards, people pick and choose what to read, if to read at all- thus they miss lots of important stuff that makes them have incomplete info to make assumptions and oppinions with. <br>
<br>
Thus, it is my conclusion that the council of guilds (and individuals are allowed of course... what the hell do you think this is bougeious of only the powerful and privalleged in guilds?) is a good thing, and something that everyone who wants to be involved in should be involved in. The voices and knowledge of the many are the key to the answer for the whole. Farming guilds and groups that dominate whatever plane/uber mob they want <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is wrong and a thing of the past</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->... Everyone has a shot now, the way it should be. Free and equal, where everyone has a say. Is there something wrong with that, honestly?<br>
<br>
PS. Verant's stance on everything is none-involvement, unless people are being harrassed, abused, or they're abusing flaws in the game. Verant doesn't support or enforce calendars, but they <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>NEVER</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> said that we couldn't organize them ourselves. They probably never even thought that a server would organize enough to create something like a serverwide council open to all. And quite frankly, I'm sure they can't/won't/wouldn't want to do anything about it. They'd probably be tickled pink to see everyone working together and solving their own problems rather than acting like asses and petitioning all the time.<br>
